    "body": "* Refactor SetMaxNRegCollector to return a structured result, including a flag for preserving explicit register settings.\r\n* Update SetMaxNRegInjector to utilize the new result structure, ensuring proper handling of register hints.\r\n* Modify logic to conditionally inject register allocation based on the presence of SIMT copies and explicit settings.\r\n* Improve test cases to validate the injection of set_max_nreg calls and ensure correct behavior in various scenarios.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Improved warp-specialization register-hint handling: explicit hints are now preserved when present; injection logic broadened to emit allocation/deallocation hints using explicit values or safe defaults, and avoids rewriting legacy hints.\n\n* **New Features**\n  * TileLang adds two explicit annotation intrinsics for producer deallocation and consumer allocation hints.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Tests updated to validate emitted script/source text and added CUDA kernel checks for correct hint placement and absence when unused.\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
